description:
As most of Spider-Man's foes are busy arguing, The Swarm decides to finish the beaten and helpless Spider-Man, covering him in bees. Dissapointed that he won't be the one to kill Spider-Man, Doctor Octopus leaves the battlefield, unaware that his cousin Hargrove is watching, and is desperate to stop him. Meanwhile the other villains; Vulture, the Beetle, Stegron, Rhino, Boomerang, Strikeback and Leila Davis, fight amongst themselves over the Nuclear Blaster. Strikeback shoots Vulture out of the sky and blows up one of Boomerang's weapons. Beetle grabs a vacant truck and throws it at Leila, who catches it and throws it back, but in her anger she misses. She continues to pummel Beetle anyway, electrocuting him and shooting him into the ground.

Boomerang is disposed of when Strikeback one of his boomerang, making him sick and knocks him out. When Leila attempts to take revenge on the paralyzed Beetle, Strikeback stops her, telling her that revenge is not the way. Suddenly Spider-Man wakes up, kicking away Swarm's bees. Suddenly Stegron attacks Slayback, crushing him in a vice grip with his tail.

Meanwhile in Dr. Octopus' secret lab on the Lower East Side of New York, Octavious is finishing up the creation of a set of Adamantium arms. Before he can put on his new weapons, the Answer breaks in. While he is shouting at Otto, the Adamantium legs sneak up from behind and capture the superhero. Back at the supervillain fight, a weakened Vulture swoops in grabbing the blaster, but he is kncoked from the sky by Rhino, who takes the blaster. Spider-Man suddenly swings into Rhino, causing him to accidently fire the blaster, hitting Swarm, killing him.

Back in Octopus' lab, Hargrove appears with a gun. Octopus easily defeats Hargrove and Answer, but before he can finish either of them off, the police arrive. Octopus flees, but Answer is shipped to the Raft. Meanwhile Strikeback defeats Stegron with a shot to the head. Spider-Man arrives and webs up Strikeback, but Leila uses the opening to fire the blaster, only to learn that Rhino used it all when he accidently killed the Swarm. Spider-Man grabs the blaster but Strikeback and Leila teleport into the future. Spidey takes one last moment to look over the defeated supervillains before leaving.
name: Re-disunited

description: Teams comprised of both G.I. Joe and Destro's operatives entered the Czech Republic in an effort to rescue the kidnapped Flint and Baroness.  While one team made headway in learning the captives' whereabouts, the other comprised of Scarlett, Daina, Paige Adams and the Crimson Twins ( Tomax/ Xamot) are set up and captured thanks to the betrayal of Lt. Gorky.  Ironically Flint and Baroness escape on their own, but will they be able to help their teammates in time?
name: The Cabal Part 2

volume.name: G.I. Joe: A Real American Hero

description: Teams comprised of G.I. Joe and Destro's operatives successfully rescue Flint and Baroness from General Moskin and his group bent on destroying Cobra Commander.  The mission does not go smoothly though as one operative is killed in the fray.  The G.I Joe team returns to America, bringing back a new agent, Daina.
name: The Cabal Part 3

volume.name: G.I. Joe: A Real American Hero

description: Storm Shadow breaks free of Cobra Commander's years of mind control and escapes to a safe house in Los Angeles. He contacts Billy, Snake-Eyes and Kamakura to get their help him enter the Arashikage mindset and permanently overcome Cobra's brainwashing. Cobra Commander discovers Storm Shadow's location and wants his ninja bodyguard back...
name: Closure 1 of 2

volume.name: G.I. Joe: A Real American Hero

description: Snake-Eyes, Kamakura and Billy attempt to help Storm Shadow, who has temporarily broken free of Cobra Commander's years of mind control. However, Cobra Commander intercepts the group before Snake-Eyes is able to secure Storm Shadow's mental state through ancient ninja techniques. A battle ensues and destroys a small part of Los Angeles, while Storm Shadow reaffirms his allegiance with Cobra, leaving Snake-Eyes to the realization that his friend is lost.
name: Closure 2 of 2

volume.name: G.I. Joe: A Real American Hero

description: General Hawk is ordered by The Jugglers to escort a group of mysterious children - who turn out to be clones of the former Cobra emperor, Serpentor - to a military base where they could be better cared for.  Believing that The Jugglers intend to actually destroy the children, Hawk defies the orders and attempts to re-route them to a safer facility.  However, the convoy transporting the children gets intercepted by none other than Serpentor; alive and looking for revenge.
name: The Last Stand 1 of 4

volume.name: G.I. Joe: A Real American Hero

description: Cobra Commander is kidnapped by Serpentor's Coil forces, with the aid of former Dreadnok - Zandar.  Serpentor reveals a horrifying plan to disable the planet's cities and finally achieve his one true ambition, global domination.  Meanwhile, General Hawk finally informs his troops about the return of G.I. Joe's greatest threat, and begins to reinstate all former agents...
name: The Last Stand 2 of 4

volume.name: G.I. Joe: A Real American Hero

description: Serpentor makes the first strike in his plan to take over the world. Meanwhile, Cobra Commander and a small group of captured G.I. Joe members escape Serpentor's prison on Cobra Island, but not without a price... a member gets seriously injured trying to protect the team.
name: The Last Stand 3 of 4

volume.name: G.I. Joe: A Real American Hero

description:
Hawk leading the G.I Joe team and Destro leading the Cobra forces join together in an assault on Cobra Island to stop Serpentor's Coil army and his plans of world domination. Cobra Island in the battlefield for three armies. After the dust settles, Serpentor is pushed out, G.I. Joe heads home and Cobra takes over the island once again. But what will happen with the children, the 9 clones of Serpentor?

Flash, Mainframe, Skidmark, and Chuckles are killed in this issue.
name: The Last Stand 4 of 4

volume.name: G.I. Joe: A Real American Hero

description: The origin of ZANYA finally told! Raised by a harsh and thoughtless mother, young Zanya has always had to fend for herself. So when she learns her father is none other than the leader of the Dreadnoks, she hits the road in search of a new life with the father she never knew. But will the road prove to be too harsh for her to travel?  After traveling across the country tracking down the Dreadnoks, Zanya and her older boyfriend Kevin finally meet up with the elusive biker gang in Kansas City. To gain admission to the rough and tough gang, fourteen year old Zanya must hold her own in a biker brawl while Kevin stands idly by, flirting with danger.
name: Family History Part 1

description: G.I. Joe Frontline expands the action of the regular G.I. JOE series into another title, featuring a cast of rotating creative teams. Frontline allows us to see the G.I. JOE universe through the eyes of different artists, and of course, it's full of action, action, action!  Despite her tough heart and quick fists, Zanya can't seem to help but bend to the will of her man, Kevin. Will she become a weak and damaged monster like her mother, or can Zanya break the cycle? And can she prove to Zartan that she's really his daughter? Join writer Sean McKeever (Sentinel, Inhumans) and artist Francis Portela (Star Wars Tales) for the finale to this two-part tale chronicling the early years of Zartan's daughter.
name: Family History Part 2

In this ONE-SHOT story, he slices, he dices, he makes up bad rhymes, and when the funding for his show is taken over by COBRA, he gets more than he asked for. It's a fun, action packed issue, as the heavy gunner/southern chef takes on TV producers, Dreadnoks and lactose intolerant pugs. Meanwhile, MAINFRAME finds out what happens when you spend too much time at the computer, and FIREWALL introduces DAINA to the joys of American culture.
name: Recipe For Destruction

description:
Overview

In the Golden Age of Hollywood, at the height of production of the great serial movie adventures, the most successful serial of all features a man in a Bat-suit, fighting crime and striking fear into the hearts of evildoers. But this "fiction" soon becomes a reality in this three-issue Elseworlds mini-series. Byron Wyatt is a successful actor/director/producer, whose independent film company, Gotham Pictures, creates the Batman serials based on the popular comic-book character. But Wyatt (who stars as the Batman) and his success threaten to undermine the big studio Arkham Pictures, run by mogul Jack "the Joker" Napier. After several threats from Napier fail to sway Wyatt from stopping production of the serials, Napier uses his mob connections for a more permanent solution to his problem. After the mob kills off the production crew and sets fire to the sets, they find Wyatt in costume and shoot him in the head. Only Wyatt doesn't die. When the actor regains consciousness from his near-fatal head wound, he has no memory of his true identity. Instead, he only remembers his life asâ¤|the Batman, and is consumed with a thirst for vengeance for the murder of his "friend," Byron Wyatt. Will his memory fully return before the ultimate confrontation with Napier? And if so, will he still have the fearlessness of the Batman to bring Napier down for good?
name: Tinseltown Terror

description:
Overview

The Elseworlds miniseries continues. Suffering a serious injury to the head, actor Byron Wyatt is now convinced he has always been his most famous role...Batman. Now "Batman" is set on getting revenge against studio mogul Jack "the Joker" Napier for Wyatt's "murder."
name: A Devil in the City of Angels

description:
Overview

The Elseworlds mini-series concludes. In the Golden Age of Hollywood, studio-magnate-turned-actor Byron Wyatt has lost himself in his on-camera character: the Batman. Meanwhile, rival studio chief Jack "the Joker" Napier makes an all-out play to take over his business.
name: Reel Trouble

description: Elseworlds Bruce Wayne is dead, and Ra's al Ghul has triumphed, billions died. But the fight continues on with Talia and her and Batman's son, Tallant.
name: Brotherhood of the Bat

description:
Overview

The Elseworlds mini-series concludes. Tallant's crime-fighting force, the League of Batmen, has been helping humanity survive a world ravaged by war and disease -- but now it's time for a final confrontation with true evil. Tallant and the League prepare for an all-out assault on the man who killed Tallant's father: the demonic Ra's al Ghul.
All of Earth's superheroes lose their powers. How? Why?

Their powers gone, their lives irrevocably changed, the once super-powered heroes of Earth struggle to retain their grasps on life, love, and in some cases, even sanity. But while the JLA members confront their personal demons, the villain known as Lex Luthor reigns as strong as ever? and is threatening not only all of "normal" humanity, but the seemingly helpless heroes as well.
